{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "name": "The Observatory",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": ["OpenSky"],
  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Mono. One voice. No chorus. No unison. Just the oscillator, the filter, and shimmer at 0.4 feedback — the hall zone. This is OPENSKY stripped of its social character: no community of unison voices, no chorus widening, no spectral smear. What remains is analytical clarity — each note's pitch, timbre, and position is legible. The observatory does not display the sky. It studies it. Use as a lead or melodic voice.",
  "tags": ["opensky", "mono", "lead", "minimal", "analytical", "aether", "guru-bin", "observatory", "clarity"],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OPENSKY — Above the Cloud Line",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "Verse 2: The Supersaw Fallacy — coherence over quantity; the single voice reveals what many voices conceal",
      "Discovery 2: Shimmer Spectrum — feedback 0.30-0.60 is hall shimmer; it ascends without disappearing",
      "Gospel 4: The Observatory Principle — remove all detuning to hear the oscillator clearly"
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "The Guru removed unison, removed chorus, removed everything except the note itself and its shimmer. What remained was more present than any padded version — more legible, more personal. The Ear said: I can hear every choice the player makes. There is nowhere to hide. The Observatory does not comfort the player. It witnesses them.",
    "diagnosis": "The Observatory is a mono lead study — unisonCount=1, chorusMix=0, no detune, no spread. FilterCutoff=8000 keeps it bright and analytical. ShimmerFeedback=0.4 adds hall-zone depth without obfuscating pitch. LFO1 at 0.067 Hz provides the single breathing modulation. This is OPENSKY as instrument, not atmosphere."
  },
